      "content": "The 2011 intervention in Libya, led by NATO and supported by the UN, aimed to protect civilians during the civil war and prevent a humanitarian disaster. In terms of geopolitical goals, it succeeded in toppling Muammar Gaddafi's regime and creating a power vacuum, which led to ongoing instability and conflict in the region. While it prevented immediate mass atrocities, it also failed to establish a stable, democratic government, resulting in a fragmented and chaotic Libya. So, in terms of achieving long-term stability and governance, the intervention can be seen as a failure.",
